  ('Partner Bump-and-Go Start', 'partner-bump-and-go-start', 'Partner Bump-and-Go Start is a non-traditional strength-based explosiveness drill selected for athletes who need to express force quickly: football linemen off the line, sprinters from a start, baseball hitters and throwers, jumpers, and field/court athletes. The goal is high-output movement quality with low fatigue, not strength grinding or conditioning volume.', 'INTERMEDIATE', 8, 3, 3, 8, 120, 135, 'Partner Bump-and-Go Start trains controlled contact stimulus into an explosive start. Use it when the session needs fresh explosiveness rather than loaded strength volume.', 'Primary subrole: Reactive Agility / Tumbling Output. Slot: reactive contact start. Coach Partner Bump-and-Go Start as Output work: high intent, low total volume, full recovery, and immediate stop when speed, posture, contact quality, or landing ownership drops.', 'Move fast, stay sharp, and own the finish. This is not a burnout set; every rep should look explosive and athletic.', 'Reactive Contact Explosiveness', 'output', 'reactive_agility_tumbling_output', 'reactive_contact_start', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_extension","knee_drive","ankle_stiffness","rib_pelvis_stack","trunk_stiffness","shoulder_horizontal_flexion"],"primary_tissues":["glutes","hamstrings","hip_flexors","quadriceps","calves","achilles_tendon"],"breathing_demand":"braced_exhale","balance_demand":"reactive_dynamic","coordination_demand":"high","impact_level":3}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Partner Bump-and-Go Start is an Output-phase explosiveness drill for controlled contact stimulus into an explosive start. The athlete performs it fresh, with maximal intent, clean positions, and enough rest that every rep stays fast.","setup":["Set a short reaction lane with cones and one clear start line.","Define the cue, finish point, and reset rule before the set starts.","Keep the stimulus simple enough that the athlete can react explosively without guessing or drifti